str2: Large, great, in the widest sense.

str2: A prolongation and middle voice form of a primary verb; to cause to be, i.e. to become, used with great latitude.
And, even, also, namely.

str2: Any one, some one, a certain one or thing. An enclitic indefinite pronoun; some or any person or object.
From gramma. A writer, i.e. scribe or secretary.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A part, portion, share. From an obsolete but more primary form of meiromai; a division or share.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Of Hebrew origin; a separatist, i.e. Exclusively religious; a Pharisean, i.e. Jewish sectary.

str2: To raise up, set up; I rise from among (the) dead; I arise, appear. From ana and histemi; to stand up.

str2: To strive greatly, contend fiercely. From dia and machomai; to fight fiercely.

str2: A prolonged form of a primary heuro, which heureo is used for it in all the tenses except the present and imperfect to find.

In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.

Or, than. A primary particle of distinction between two connected terms; disjunctive, or; comparative, than.

str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
